This version removes the change set after an element has been deleted and checks if there are any remaining changes in the first (and presumably only) change set of the session model. If not, it calls `deleteChangeSet` to remove the now-empty change set. 

If multiple change sets are possible or other complexities apply, further adjustments might be necessary based on specifics of the application's data model and requirements that aren't fully detailed here.
